<Review>My now fiance and I have been together for 7 years and we had talked about getting married, but hadn't done anything to actually make it happen until one day he tells me he'd like to take me ring shopping, because he wants me to get the ring I want. I was blown away, I had never thought about picking my own engagement ring, nor had I ever thought about what kind of ring I would want, so I had a lot to think about. I knew that getting a certified diamond was important to me, and some certifications are better than others, I even started think seriously about lab created diamonds because of all the unknown variables with mined diamonds. Basically I was running in circles in my mind not getting anywhere, so we finally decided to just go in to a Kay at the outlet mall when we were there for other reasons. I liked what they had, but didn't find anything that spoke to me, so we went to the mall, and tried almost every jewelry store there, with a few terrible experiences, and a few distant possibilities, but still nothing that really spoke to me. I saw the Leo diamond at Kay, and was leaning towards settling for that when I decided to search jewelry stores that carry Leo diamonds, and Jared came up so instead of dismissing them because they were far away my fiance suggested we go look since we would be in that area in a few days, that was the best decision we made! We were promptly greeted by Ric, who offered us coffee or water, and took us to a little office to get a feel for what we were looking for, how much we wanted to spend, and to explain a little more about Jared and all the reasons we should choose them. My fiance loves the extras, so he was immediately happy, I like people who make me feel comfortable, and listen to what I'm saying, so I very quickly felt happy with our decision to give Jared a shot as Ric had ideas, and brought in Mel who had more ideas, and between the four of us Jared customized a beautiful diamond band to add a setting for a beautiful rectangular brilliant cut diamond, and I couldn't be more happy with the final product than I am! The ring was ready in 24 hours, although we didn't pick it up for a few days, and I can't stop looking at my ring! Thank you Ric and Mel, you guys are great and my fiance and I are both happy beyond words!<//Review></record>

<GmapID>0x80dcd77f86c1089f:0x86ca4f1be4ee6a30</GmapID><Pics>None<//Pics>< Name>
alejandro ramirez<//Name>
< Review>
Atmosphere was good for taco Tuesday. The DJ was really trying to get the guests entertained and engaged. Several times mentioned birthdays and tried to get everyone excited for the birthday people. (For people like me that cheer people on their birthdays while at restaurants, it was fun) repeated that he takes song requests via Instagram which was cool because he played different genres but in well order; He didn't mix them like a vegetable medley.
The Camarones ala Diabla were good, very spicy, great flavor profile, and the shrimp were cooked to perfection. The shrimp were not overly cooked nor under but for the price, I must say too much even if it is located near Disneyland. The rice served was clearly reheated. I won't say it was from the day before but definitely cooked and sat for a while. If I had to guess, they made a large batch and kept reheating throughout the day. Not only was the rice mediocre but they only served one cup of rice. As I said I went on taco Tuesday so I had to try the tacos, for the dollar deal they were good. I was enjoying my shrimp until I was given the salsa for the tacos. The red salsa given to me was the same one they use for the Camarones ala Diabla. So basically, I paid extra to have my shrimp swimming in sauce that they give for free to guests. If i had to say i paid 28 dollars for a 7 dollar plate if I would have cooked it at home myself; that is buying at retail price at a rural supermarket for the ingredients, not wholesale like restaurants do. I stated to the waitress that I wanted bacon wrapped shrimp for the appetizer, instead I get the dinner meal which was more than 2 times more the app price. I would have returned the food but you know that's always a big no no. So when ordering an appetizer always make sure that it isn't also listed as a main entr√©e and if it is, reiterate several times that you want the appetizer.
The pepino con limon drink was good for a mixed drink but the pepino flavor was missing. The name is deceiving. The sprite I order has heavy in taste of fountain water, tasted weird.
The server was rude in the beginning. I asked for what non alcoholic drinks they have and she gave me a glance that was meant to be daggers. She didn't answer me so I asked if they had her horchata, she smirked and said they don't carry those types of drinks there. The rest of the time she was good, since she only dropped off the food and refilled the drink once. Out of the hour and a half I was there I only talked to her 3 or 4 times. She looked like the 40 year old women that go to nightclubs and think everyone should bow to them.
So to sum up, the only really good thing was the DJ his dynamic is definitely worth 4 stars alone but everything else was isnt even worth a star.</Review>

<text>Everyone hates the dentist. Or so I thought. My experience here was actually a positive one. After calling several offices, I found Aava dental through my dental insurance. I was able to get in for an appointment the next day!

Once in the office, the staff made me feel welcome. They were sooo friendly and got to know me and built a relationship with me. They were very accommodating for my future appointments.

The dentist was gentle, gave me breaks so I can shut my mouth and he didn't ask me questions while working on my mouth! (A big plus for me, because I would rather not talk when hands and tools are in my mouth)

Now I would like to note that I have been cursed with bad teeth. Almost every time I go to the dentist, it costs a fortune. And now that I am moved out of the house, I am responsible for paying my own bills (sad day). the dentist told me all the work I was going to need, I cringed at the thought of how much it would cost. (And no he was not scamming me into things I didn't need, it was expected considering how long it had been since I'd been to the dentist and how my dental history has been) After he told me what needed to be done, the office manager came in and went over the prices of the procedures, how much insurance would cover, etc. WOW. My mind was blown. It was at a fraction of what I thought it was going to cost.

To conclude, the staff was friendly and efficient, the dentist was knowledgeable and gentle and the prices were reasonable. I would definitely recommend this office to friends and family!<//text>< pictures>

<review>My experience here was really great! Helen gave me a massage. She was very thorough and made sure I was very comfortable. I got a 70 minute massage for $40 which is an excellent price. I went to Wells Fargo Bank.  It was on a busy Saturday afternoon.  As I arrived, a car was pulling out located facing entryway to bank.  I was quickly greeted with how can I be assisted my name was written on await list to speak to a banks rep. Wait was 45 mins. For a extremely busy day I guess the wait was normal.  Everyone was cordial and helpful.  Customers have a variety of language reps available to them when needed.  Great for excellent customer care.</review>

<rating>3<//rating>< review>
The shopping mall is exactly what the economic demographic of the area dictates. There was a Grocery Outlet which is a blessing in the neighborhood where there are rather eclectic stores in the direct vicinity. There was also a Dollar Tree which if you're not in a hurry can serve your needs. There's also a DD discount store and a 24 Hour Fitness, which I hear has improved since I was there but three or four years ago I know it was horrible. There's also a liquor store which is one of the more friendly in the neighborhood and I had fun there a while back and it wasn't bad. The neighborhood is probably like you to have this place to make ends meet.<//review>
